    <section id="content" class="pb-80">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-8">
            <div class="text-block mb-50">
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20 font-weight-bold color-secondary">
                Advanced Critical Care for Liver Patients
              </p>
              <div class="video-banner-layout3 bg-overlay mb-50">
                <img src="/assets/images/banners/11.jpg" alt="ICU Facility" loading="lazy" width="800" height="450">
                <a class="video__btn video__btn-white popup-video" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nrJtHemSPW4">
                  <div class="video__player">
                    <i class="fa fa-play"></i>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </div><!-- /.video-banner -->
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Our Intensive Care Unit (ICU) is specifically designed to care for critically ill patients, especially those with severe liver disease or recovering from major liver surgery like transplantation. It is staffed 24/7 by a team of critical care specialists, nurses, and respiratory therapists.
              </p>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                The ICU is equipped with advanced monitoring systems, mechanical ventilators, and life-support equipment to provide the highest level of care. We are committed to ensuring the safety, comfort, and best possible outcomes for our most vulnerable patients.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">ICU Facilities and Equipment</h5>
              <ul class="list-items list-unstyled mb-40 pl-40">
                <li><strong>Private ICU Beds:</strong> Individual rooms with glass partitions for patient privacy while maintaining constant monitoring.</li>
                <li><strong>Advanced Monitoring Systems:</strong> Continuous cardiac, respiratory, and hemodynamic monitoring with telemetry.</li>
                <li><strong>Mechanical Ventilators:</strong> Latest generation ventilators for respiratory support.</li>
                <li><strong>Dialysis Equipment:</strong> Continuous renal replacement therapy (CRRT) for patients with kidney failure.</li>
                <li><strong>Central Monitoring Station:</strong> Real-time monitoring of all patients from centralized station.</li>
                <li><strong>Specialized Beds:</strong> ICU beds with pressure-relief mattresses to prevent bedsores.</li>
                <li><strong>Point-of-Care Testing:</strong> Bedside blood gas analysis and laboratory testing for rapid results.</li>
              </ul>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">ICU Team</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Our multidisciplinary ICU team includes:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-items list-unstyled mb-40 pl-40">
                <li><strong>Critical Care Physicians (Intensivists):</strong> Board-certified specialists trained in intensive care medicine, available 24/7.</li>
                <li><strong>Transplant Surgeons:</strong> For post-operative liver transplant patients.</li>
                <li><strong>Hepatologists:</strong> Liver specialists managing acute liver failure and complications of cirrhosis.</li>
                <li><strong>ICU Nurses:</strong> Specially trained critical care nurses with 1:1 or 1:2 patient ratios.</li>
                <li><strong>Respiratory Therapists:</strong> Managing ventilators and respiratory support.</li>
                <li><strong>Pharmacists:</strong> Clinical pharmacists for medication management.</li>
                <li><strong>Physiotherapists:</strong> Early mobilization and chest physiotherapy.</li>
                <li><strong>Nutritionists:</strong> Specialized enteral and parenteral nutrition support.</li>
              </ul>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Conditions Treated in ICU</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                <strong>Post-Liver Transplant Care:</strong> Immediate post-operative monitoring after liver transplantation, managing immunosuppression, and preventing complications. Most transplant patients spend 2-5 days in ICU.
              </p>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                <strong>Acute Liver Failure:</strong> Intensive monitoring and support for patients with rapid deterioration of liver function, managing hepatic encephalopathy, cerebral edema, and multi-organ support.
              </p>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                <strong>Decompensated Cirrhosis:</strong> Severe complications of cirrhosis including variceal bleeding, hepatorenal syndrome, spontaneous bacterial peritonitis, and hepatic encephalopathy requiring ICU-level care.
              </p>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                <strong>Post-Major Surgery:</strong> Recovery after complex hepatobiliary and pancreatic surgeries requiring close monitoring.
              </p>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                <strong>Sepsis and Multi-Organ Failure:</strong> Comprehensive management of septic shock and organ support.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Advanced Life Support</h5>
              <ul class="list-items list-unstyled mb-40 pl-40">
                <li><strong>Mechanical Ventilation:</strong> Invasive and non-invasive ventilation strategies for respiratory failure.</li>
                <li><strong>Vasopressor Support:</strong> Medications to maintain blood pressure in shock states.</li>
                <li><strong>Continuous Dialysis (CRRT):</strong> 24-hour dialysis for kidney failure and fluid management.</li>
                <li><strong>Plasmapheresis:</strong> Blood filtration for certain liver conditions.</li>
                <li><strong>Intracranial Pressure Monitoring:</strong> For patients with cerebral edema from liver failure.</li>
                <li><strong>ECMO (Extracorporeal Membrane Oxygenation):</strong> Available for selected cases of severe respiratory or cardiac failure.</li>
              </ul>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Infection Control</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Our ICU maintains the highest standards of infection control with HEPA filtration, positive pressure rooms for immunocompromised patients, strict hand hygiene protocols, and antimicrobial stewardship to prevent hospital-acquired infections. All equipment is sterilized using validated processes.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Family-Centered Care</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                We believe in involving families in patient care. Designated visiting hours allow family members to be with their loved ones. Our team provides regular updates on patient progress. For stable patients, we encourage family participation in simple care activities under nursing supervision.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Step-Down Unit</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                As patients improve, they transition to our high-dependency unit (HDU) or step-down unit for continued monitoring before moving to the general ward. This progressive care model ensures smooth recovery and optimal resource utilization.
              </p>
